---
id: org.dxos.plugin.product-search
name: ProductSearchPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A Composer plugin for structured product search across configurable vendor sites.
Users configure **Providers** (search site templates), compose a **Search** across
one or more of them, and get back a list of **Results**. Providers are authored
once — either by the user or via an LLM blueprint that derives the template by
inspecting the vendor site — and reused across many searches.

Supported verticals include retail (products), automotive listings, real estate,
or any site whose results can be reached by HTTP GET/POST and parsed from HTML
or JSON.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |

## Types

```mdl
type Provider
  desc: >
    A configured search site. Contains a typed search-field schema plus the
    request and result mappings needed to turn criteria into listings.
    Providers of kind 'api' call a JSON endpoint; kind 'scrape' parse HTML.
    Templates are authored by the AnalyzeProvider blueprint or edited manually
    via ProviderArticle.
  fields:
    name: string
    url: string
    description?: string
    kind: 'api' | 'scrape'
    enabled: boolean
    searchSchema?: JsonSchema       # typed fields the user fills in (criteria form)
    request?: RequestMapping        # binds criteria values to HTTP request
    result?: ResultMapping          # extracts result rows from the HTTP response
  annotations:
    icon: ph--globe--regular
    hue: cyan
    label: name
    blueprint: org.dxos.plugin.product-search/blueprint/provider
```

```mdl
type RequestMapping
  desc: Describes how to build the HTTP request from criteria values.
  fields:
    method: 'GET' | 'POST'
    urlTemplate: string             # may embed {field} tokens
    query?: Record<string, FieldBinding>
    body?: Record<string, FieldBinding>
    headers?: Record<string, string>
```

```mdl
type FieldBinding
  desc: Maps one criteria field to one request parameter with an optional transform hint.
  fields:
    field: string
    transform?: string              # e.g. 'min', 'max', '{value}/page'
```

```mdl
type ResultMapping
  desc: Describes how to extract listing rows from the HTTP response.
  fields:
    responseType: 'html' | 'json'
    itemLocator: string             # CSS selector (html) or JSONPath (json)
    fields: Record<string, FieldExtractor>
```

```mdl
type FieldExtractor
  desc: Extracts one field value relative to a located item.
  fields:
    selector?: string               # CSS selector relative to item (html)
    attr?: string                   # HTML attribute to read; omit for text content
    path?: string                   # JSONPath relative to item (json)
```

```mdl
type Search
  desc: >
    A saved search configuration. Holds provider refs and the typed criteria
    values (keyed by field name from the union of provider schemas). Results
    are stored as Ref<Result> links — running the search replaces them.
  fields:
    name: string
    providers: Ref<Provider>[]
    criteria: Record<string, unknown>   # typed values keyed by field name
    results: Ref<Result>[]
    status?: 'idle' | 'running' | 'error'
    lastRunAt?: string                  # ISO 8601
  annotations:
    icon: ph--magnifying-glass--regular
    hue: cyan
    label: name
```

```mdl
type Result
  desc: >
    A single product listing returned by a provider search. Linked back to the
    Search via Search.results. Stores extracted fields plus the raw key/value
    properties map for any extra data the mapping produces.
  fields:
    title: string
    url: string
    price?: number
    currency?: string
    images: string[]
    provider?: Ref<Provider>
    properties: Record<string, unknown>
    fetchedAt?: string              # ISO 8601
  annotations:
    icon: ph--tag--regular
    hue: cyan
    label: title
```

## Components

```mdl
component SearchArticle
  desc: >
    Master/detail article surface for a Search object. Left pane has a
    provider-select multi-checkbox and a dynamic criteria form built from the
    union of selected provider schemas. Right pane shows a Masonry grid of
    ResultCard tiles. Detail opens in a companion pane when a tile is clicked.
  props:
    search: Search
  state:
    running: boolean
    selectedResult?: Result
  actions:
    runSearch()                     # invokes RunSearch operation
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Providers (checkboxes)  │  [🔍 Search]               │
    │ [field1] [field2] ...   │                            │
    │ ─────────────────────── │                            │
    │ Criteria form           │  Masonry grid of tiles     │
    │                         │                            │
    └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component ResultCard
  desc: >
    Masonry tile for a single Result. Shows the first image (if any), title,
    price, and a selection of key properties. Click opens ResultDetail.
  props:
    result: Result
    provider?: Provider             # resolved for display name
  emits:
    onOpen(result: Result)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [image if present]      │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ Title (2-line clamp)    │
    │ Price                   │
    │ key: value …            │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component ProviderArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface for editing a Provider. Shows name/url/kind fields plus
    a code-editor region for the raw searchSchema, request, and result
    mappings. An 'Analyze' toolbar button triggers the AnalyzeProvider blueprint
    to auto-derive the template from the live site.
  props:
    provider: Provider
  actions:
    analyze()                       # invokes AnalyzeProvider → SetProviderTemplate
```

## Services

```mdl
service AnalyzeProviderBlueprint
  desc: >
    LLM blueprint that derives a Provider's template from the live vendor site.
    Triggered by the Analyze button in ProviderArticle or by a user chat message.
    The agent calls AnalyzeProvider (which fetches the page source), then calls
    SetProviderTemplate to persist the derived schema + mappings.
  key: org.dxos.plugin.product-search/blueprint/provider
  ops:
    # Tools exposed to the agent:
    # - AnalyzeProvider    (fetch page source)
    # - SetProviderTemplate (persist template)
```

## Operations

```mdl
op AnalyzeProvider
  desc: >
    Fetches the provider's vendor site via the edge proxy and returns the
    page HTML/JSON source. Pure read — does not mutate the Provider. Used by
    the blueprint agent as the inspection step before deriving the template.
  input:
    provider: Ref<Provider>
  output: string                    # raw page source
  effects: [http, echo:read]
```

```mdl
op SetProviderTemplate
  desc: >
    Persists a derived template onto a Provider: sets searchSchema, request
    mapping, and result mapping in one atomic write.
  input:
    provider: Ref<Provider>
    searchSchema: JsonSchema
    request: RequestMapping
    result: ResultMapping
  output: Ref<Provider>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op RunProviderSearch
  desc: >
    Executes one provider template against a Search's criteria. Binds the
    criteria values to the request mapping, fetches the endpoint via the edge
    proxy, parses the response with the result mapping, and persists the
    resulting Result objects in the space.
  input:
    search: Ref<Search>
    provider: Ref<Provider>
  output: Ref<Result>[]
  effects: [http, echo:write]
  note: >
    Skips providers where enabled === false or where request/result mappings
    are absent (template not yet derived).
```

```mdl
op RunSearch
  desc: >
    Fan-out orchestrator. Clears the Search's existing results, then invokes
    RunProviderSearch in parallel for each enabled provider reference. Writes
    the union of returned Result refs back onto Search.results. Sets
    Search.status and Search.lastRunAt. Runs deterministically — no LLM needed.
    Can be triggered from the UI or by an agent (scheduleable).
  input:
    search: Ref<Search>
  output: void
  effects: [echo:write, echo:read]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Provider Templates
  desc: Users configure Provider objects with typed search fields and HTTP mappings.

  req F-1.1: User can create a Provider object via the plugin's create menu.
  req F-1.2: Provider.kind is 'api' or 'scrape'.
  req F-1.3: Provider.searchSchema is a JSONSchema describing criteria fields; drives the form.
  req F-1.4: Provider.request maps criteria values to HTTP request parameters.
  req F-1.5: Provider.result maps the HTTP response to a list of result rows.
  req F-1.6: Provider.enabled defaults to true; disabled providers are skipped by RunSearch.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Blueprint-Derived Templates
  desc: LLM agent derives Provider template from the live site.

  req F-2.1: AnalyzeProvider fetches the vendor site and returns page source.
  req F-2.2: SetProviderTemplate persists searchSchema + request + result in one write.
  req F-2.3: ProviderArticle Analyze button triggers the blueprint flow.
  req F-2.4: After SetProviderTemplate, the provider is ready for RunProviderSearch.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Search Execution
  desc: RunSearch fans out to all enabled providers and links results.

  req F-3.1: SearchArticle toolbar includes a Run Search button.
  req F-3.2: Clicking Run Search sets Search.status to 'running' and disables the button.
  req F-3.3: RunSearch invokes RunProviderSearch for each enabled provider in the Search.
  req F-3.4: Results from all providers are merged into Search.results (refs).
  req F-3.5: After completion Search.status returns to 'idle' and Search.lastRunAt is set.
  req F-3.6: Provider failures are non-fatal; the search continues with remaining providers.
  req F-3.7: Empty Search.providers disables the Run Search button.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Criteria Form
  desc: Dynamic form built from the union of selected providers' search schemas.

  req F-4.1: SearchArticle computes the union of searchSchema fields from selected providers.
  req F-4.2: The criteria form renders one input per union field using the field type from JSONSchema.
  req F-4.3: Range fields (min/max) render as a RangeField component.
  req F-4.4: Criteria values are stored in Search.criteria keyed by field name.
  req F-4.5: Changing provider selection recomputes the union; orphaned criteria values are preserved.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Results Display
  desc: Masonry grid of ResultCard tiles; detail pane for selected result.

  req F-5.1: SearchArticle renders Search.results as a Masonry grid of ResultCard tiles.
  req F-5.2: Each tile shows the first image (if any), title, price, and key properties.
  req F-5.3: Clicking a tile opens ResultDetail in a companion/detail pane.
  req F-5.4: Empty state shown when Search.results is empty.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create Provider
  given: user is in a space in Composer
  when: user creates a Provider via the plugin's create menu
  then:
    - Provider object created in space with enabled = true
    - searchSchema, request, result are undefined (template not yet set)
```

```mdl
test T-2: SetProviderTemplate persists template
  given: a Provider with no template
  when: SetProviderTemplate is called with searchSchema, request, result
  then:
    - Provider.searchSchema equals the input schema
    - Provider.request equals the input mapping
    - Provider.result equals the input mapping
```

```mdl
test T-3: RunProviderSearch skips untemplate'd provider
  given: a Provider where request and result are undefined
  when: RunProviderSearch is called
  then: returns an empty result array without making any HTTP request
```

```mdl
test T-4: RunSearch fans out and links results
  given: a Search with two enabled providers, both with valid templates
  when: RunSearch is called
  then:
    - RunProviderSearch invoked once per provider
    - Search.results contains refs to all returned Result objects
    - Search.status is 'idle'
    - Search.lastRunAt is set to an ISO timestamp
```

```mdl
test T-5: RunSearch is non-fatal on provider error
  given: a Search with two providers; one returns an HTTP 500
  when: RunSearch is called
  then:
    - Results from the successful provider appear in Search.results
    - Search.status is 'idle' (not 'error')
```

```mdl
test T-6: Criteria form union
  given: a Search with two providers whose schemas share one field and each add one unique field
  when: SearchArticle renders the criteria form
  then:
    - Form shows three fields total (one shared + two unique)
    - No duplicate field rendered
```

```mdl
test T-7: Run Search button disabled without providers
  given: a Search with an empty providers array
  when: SearchArticle renders
  then: Run Search button is disabled
```

---

## Design Notes

### Template Authoring

Provider templates are the central configuration artifact. Two authoring paths
exist:

- **Blueprint path (agent-assisted).** The `AnalyzeProvider` blueprint fetches
  the vendor site and derives `searchSchema`, `request`, and `result` mappings
  via an LLM. The agent uses two tools (`AnalyzeProvider` for fetch, then
  `SetProviderTemplate` to persist). Triggered from ProviderArticle's Analyze
  button or via chat.
- **Manual path.** The user edits the raw mappings directly in ProviderArticle.
  Useful when the vendor site is behind auth or when the user knows the API
  structure precisely.

### Request Binding

`bindRequest` compiles `RequestMapping` against `Search.criteria` to produce a
concrete `{ method, url, headers, body }` request descriptor. Field tokens are
resolved from criteria; transforms (`min`, `max`, format templates) are applied
at binding time. Unknown criteria keys that don't appear in the mapping are
silently ignored.

### Result Extraction

`extractResults` accepts the raw HTTP response body and a `ResultMapping`. For
`html` responses, CSS selectors locate items and fields; for `json` responses,
JSONPath expressions are used. The result is an array of `ResultData` objects
with well-known fields (`title`, `url`, `price`, `currency`, `images`) plus a
`properties` bag for extras. Extraction errors for individual items are silently
skipped (partial results are better than no results).

### Edge Proxy

All outbound HTTP requests are routed through the DXOS edge proxy via
`fetchViaProxy`. This avoids CORS restrictions when searches run client-side and
provides a uniform path for rate-limiting or credential injection in a future
revision.

### Criteria Union

`buildUnionSchema` computes the union of `searchSchema` fields from the
selected providers. Fields with matching names are merged (first-seen type
wins). This is how a cross-provider criteria form is possible: providers
covering the same vertical tend to share field names (`make`, `model`,
`minPrice`, `maxPrice`).

### Scheduleable Searches

`RunSearch` is a pure operation (no UI dependency). It can be invoked by an
agent on a schedule — the user creates a Search, configures providers and
criteria, and asks the agent to run it periodically. Results accumulate across
runs (dedup by URL is an optional future extension).

### Out of Scope

- Result deduplication across providers or runs.
- Authenticated vendor requests (would require credential storage in Provider).
- Pagination — first page only per provider per run.
- Saved result snapshots / history (results are replaced on each run).
